Name: Plating
Description: How to create beautiful and eyecatching dishes!

Name: Alternative cooking techniques
Description: Unconventional ways to cook delicious food

Name: Stove-top cooking
Description: Techniques to cook on the stove top, a direct and constant source of heat.

Name: Oven cooking
Description: Techniques to make the best food on the oven.

Name: Prepping techniques
Description: Every technique that is related to the before-cooking part of the creation of a dish

Name: Mixing
Description: Mixing techniques (easy and hard ones) that create a range of effects in you dish.

Name: Preserving
Description: Ways to preserve your food properly to create the most diverse effects on flavour and texture!

Name: Seasoning
Description: How to accentuate and increment the flavours in your dish!

Name: Chopping
Description: All different types of cuts: dicing, mincing, baton, chiffonade, ...

Name: Appliances
Description: Blenders, processors, mixer and other eletronic home appliances!

Name: Storage
Description: Fridges, freezers and other equipments that help store your food

Name: Heating equipment
Description: Everything that generates heat in order to cook your food. Stoves, oven, barbecue grill, microwave, ...

Name: Disposables
Description: Cling film, parchment paper and other one time use equipments.

Name: Containers
Description: Bowls, trays and other equipments that hold the food you're cooking!

Name: Pots and pans
Description: Frying pans, sauce pans, stock pots and everything you use to cook on a stove!

Name: Utensils
Description: Kitchen equipment that you use along other equipments. Includes spatula, whisk, cutting board and others.

Name: Cutting tools
Description: Everything with a blade: chefs knife, paring knife, peeler, grader, ...

Name: Bread, flour and pasta
Description: Flours and ingredients that derive from it: dried pasta and different tupes of bread!

Name: Sweeteners and chocolate
Description: Sugars, sweeteners, chocolates and all that sweet goodness!

Name: Stocks and sauces
Description: A good stock can pack your meal with deliciousness. Sauces add texture and flavour to the final dish!

Name: Cooking alcohols
Description: A diverse variety of cooking wines, bourbons, sakes and many other drinks.

Name: Seasoning ingredients
Description: Salt, herbs, chili flakes, black pepper, ... You name it!

Name: Condiments
Description: Vinegar, ketchup, mustard and other condiments you may have in your pantry.

Name: Fats and oils
Description: Butter and vegetable oils and pastes. They bring flavours together and add loads to your dish.

Name: Dairy
Description: Products derived from milk! Being it cow's milk or goat's milk. All types of chesses, yoghurts, creams and much more.

Name: Eggs
Description: Classic ingredient. Most famous one is the chicken egg, but you'll find use for quail eggs and others.

Name: Seafood
Description: Prawns, oysters, clams and everything that comes from the bottom of the ocean!

Name: Fish
Description: Clean source of protein and good fats, fish is one of the most diverse cathegory you'll find!

Name: Pork
Description: Bacon, pork ribs, panceta, you name it! Delicous and mostly fatty cuts.

Name: Beef
Description: Delicious cuts with a intense red colour.

Name: Chicken
Description: Chicken and other poutry cuts, such as duck!

Name: Funghi
Description: Basically mushrooms. Neither animal nor vegetable but delicious afterall.

Name: Legumes
Description: An specific type of seeds, that comes in a pod. Includes peas, beans and others!

Name: Seeds and Grains
Description: Rice, nuts and much else!

Name: Fresh herbs
Description: Basil, mint, rosemary, thyme. Fresh herbs, with soft or hard stalk, that bring flavour to your dish!

Name: Fruits
Description: Apples, bananas, strawberries and much much more!

Name: (not) Veggies
Description: Tomatoes and cucumbers are fruits and peppers are berries. Technically these are not veggies, but we use them as if they were!

Name: Greens
Description: Leafy (lettuce, spinach, ...) and stem (aspargus, broccoli, ...) greens!

Name: Bulbs
Description: Underground part of some plants, rich in simple sugars. You may know them as Onions and Garlic

Name: Root Vegetables
Description: Carrots, potatoes, turnips ... All of those heartwarming roots that you know and love!
